EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to educational personnel; authorizing a person
who holds a license to teach in certain states to be hired as
a teacher in this State if he or she satisfies certain
requirements; authorizing a person to simultaneously
enroll in multiple programs for an alternative route to
licensure; requiring the Commission on Professional
Standards in Education to prescribe certain regulations
concerning the licensure of teachers, school nurses and
school social workers; and providing other matters
properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law creates the Commission on Professional Standards in Education
2 and requires the Commission to prescribe regulations for licensing teachers and
3 other educational personnel. (NRS 391.011, 391.019) Under existing law, such
4 regulations are required to provide for the reciprocal licensure of educational
5 personnel from other states. (NRS 391.032) Section 1 of this bill requires the
6 Commission to compile a list of states in which the requirements and qualifications
7 to obtain a license to teach are equivalent to the requirements and qualifications to
8 obtain a license to teach in this State. Section 1 additionally authorizes the board of
9 trustees of a school district or the governing body of a charter school to employ as a
10 teacher a person not licensed as a teacher in this State if the person: (1) holds a
11 license in good standing from a state included on the list compiled by the
12 Commission; (2) has submitted an application to receive a license to teach in this
13 State; and (3) has completed the background investigation the employing school
14 district is required to conduct.
15 Section 2 of this bill requires that the regulations adopted by the Commission
16 also prescribe qualifications for a person who holds certain licenses to teach to
-
