17 receive a license to teach elementary education without repeating previously
18 completed requirements or satisfying additional requirements. Section 2
19 additionally requires such regulations to prescribe qualifications for a person to use
20 work experience or a license in an area of career and technical education to receive
21 an endorsement in career and technical education without repeating certain
22 requirements. Section 2 also requires such regulations to authorize a person to
23 serve as a school nurse or school social worker without the applicable endorsement
24 if the person: (1) has applied for such an endorsement but the endorsement has not
25 yet been approved or denied; and (2) holds certain valid licenses issued by the State
26 Board of Nursing or the Board of Examiners for Social Workers, as applicable.
27 Section 4 of this bill makes a conforming change to authorize such a registered
28 nurse to be employed as a school nurse without an endorsement as a school nurse.
29 Existing law requires the Commission to prescribe regulations that set forth the
30 qualifications for licensing teachers through an alternative route to licensure. (NRS
31 391.019) Section 2 requires such regulations to authorize a person to
32 simultaneously enroll in multiple programs for an alternative route to licensure.
33 Section 3 of this bill requires a reduction in the fee for a license to teach for
34 certain applicants who are substitute teachers.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 391 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. The Commission shall develop, and on an annual basis,
4 update a list of each state that the Commission determines has
5 requirements and qualifications for a license to teach early
6 childhood education, elementary education, middle school or
7 junior high school education, secondary education or special
8 education that are substantially equivalent to the requirements
9 and qualifications for such a license in this State.
10 2. Notwithstanding any other provision of law, the board of
11 trustees of a school district or the governing body of a charter
12 school may, on a provisional basis not to exceed 1 year, employ as
13 a teacher a person who is not licensed to teach pursuant to this
14 chapter if the person:
15 (a) Is licensed in good standing as a teacher in a state included
16 on the most recent list developed or updated by the Commission
17 pursuant to subsection 1;
18 (b) Has submitted an application for the issuance of a license
19 to teach pursuant to this chapter;
20 (c) Is employed to teach in a position that corresponds to the
21 license of the teacher in the other state;
22 (d) Complies with the requirements of NRS 391.104; and
23 (e) Is not otherwise prohibited from being employed as a
24 teacher in this State.
